Standards-Version: 4.6.2
Rules-Requires-Root: no
Homepage: https://github.com/arhebs/epoll-echo

Package: epoll-echo
Architecture: any
Depends: ${shlibs:Depends}, ${misc:Depends}
Description: Single-process TCP/UDP echo server built on epoll
 epoll-echo provides a single-process daemon that concurrently
 handles TCP line clients and UDP datagrams using the Linux epoll
 API. It includes guarded administrative commands, journald-friendly
 logging, and optional systemd socket activation support, making it
 a handy example and diagnostic tool for modern networking stacks.
